{{Infobox ancient site|type = {{ill|Round Kofun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft}}| name=Maruyamazuka Kofun| image={{image requested|cat=Yame City}}| Cluster={{ill|Yame Kofun Cluster|ja|八女古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}}| location={{ill|Yame City|ja|八女市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Japan| coordinates={{ill|coordinates|ja|座標|qq=draft|qq=draft}}: {{Coord|33|13|57.6|N|130|34|09.4|E}}| type=Round Kofun (円墳)| area=Diameter a11rox. 33 meters| built=Late {{ill|6th century|ja|6世紀|qq=draft|qq=draft}}| burial=Two-chambered {{ill|Yokoana-style Stone Chamber|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft|qq=draft}}| Historic site =Designated as a national {{ill|Historic site of Japan|ja|史跡|1=Historic site|lt=Historic site of Japan|qq=draft|qq=draft}}} in [[Shōwa]] 53 (1978)| Special Features=Decorated tumulus }}
'''Maruyamazuka Kofun''' (丸山塚古墳) is a round tumulus ({{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) located in {{ill|Yame City|ja|八女市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Japan. It is part of the {{ill|Yame Kofun Cluster|ja|八女古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and has been Historic site as a national {{ill|Historic site of Japan|ja|史跡|1=Historic site|lt=Historic site of Japan|qq=draft|qq=draft}}}.
== Overview == The Maruyamazuka Kofun is a large round tumulus with a diameter of approximately 33 meters and a height of about 5.3 meters. It is believed to have originally been surrounded by a moat and embankment<ref name=iwato>"Iwato Historical Museum Exhibit Catalogue," p. 27.</ref>. Located 200 meters north of this tumulus are the {{ill|Zenzōzuka Kofun|ja|善蔵塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Chausuzuka Kofun|ja|茶臼塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, both of which are also Historic site as national historic sites<ref name=genchi>On-site explanation panel.</ref>.
The burial facility is a two-chambered {{ill|Yokoana-style Stone Chamber|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, measuring 8 meters in total length and opening to the south<ref name=genchi>On-site explanation panel.</ref>. Similar to the {{ill|Noriba Kofun|ja|乗場古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, it features a multi-chamber structure with a front and rear room. Large stones were used for the base, while flat stones were stacked in a dome type using the split-stone construction technique. Additionally, the inner walls of the back wall, burial chamber, and entrance chamber were decorated with patterns such as triangular motifs, circular designs, and fern patterns in red, yellow, and green. To preserve the stone chamber, it was reburied after investigation, and entry is currently not allowed<ref name=iwato>"Iwato Historical Museum Exhibit Catalogue," p. 27.</ref>.
The Maruyamazuka Kofun is estimated to have been constructed in the late {{ill|6th century|ja|6世紀|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, slightly later than the {{ill|Kōkadani Kofun|ja|弘化谷古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Hirokawa Town (Fukuoka Prefecture)|ja|広川町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, based on the multi-chamber structure of the stone chamber<ref name=iwato>"Iwato Historical Museum Exhibit Catalogue," p. 27.</ref>.
